My TOP TWO TIPS for building CONFIDENCE 💗🪩💃

1️⃣ Get clear on WHO YOU ARE☝️
The more clarity you gain about who you are, and who God’s made you to be, the less you start questioning your actions and feeling like you’re lacking. Coming into alignment with your inner most being, healing the inside and uncovering the lies you’ve believed about yourself, are all automatic confidence upgrades. While faking it till you make it has value in many situations, we can’t solely base our confidence on our works alone and what we do on the external. The inside has to match the outside.  
2️⃣ Do it afraid and show up even when it feels uncomfortable!! 👊🏼
This might sound like a contradiction, but I feel like there is an important balance of leaning into who you are, doing the inner work AND taking action at the same time. The thing about action is that it can also be an amazing guide and teacher. You will learn more about yourself, gain more clarity, which in turn will send you on an upward confidence spiral.  Clarity in who you are = Confidence  Action when aligned and on a healing path = More Clarity = More Confidence.   When you combine action with inner work, you will be unstoppable.  
Has your lack of confidence ever stopped you from pursuing your dreams? Comment below ⬇️💗
Do you agree? 👀💗

How many times have you gone to either put yourself out there or post a reel only to talk yourself off the edge, or save to drafts?

It’s these micro moments we face over and over that start to shift our belief about ourselves. We go from “I can’t do that!” Or “I did it.”

And we learn that in the end, that we start to care less about the outcome and more about the fact that we overcame.

So today I’m sharing a video that’s been in MY drafts and I want to challenge you to take action on something today that scares you.

If you’re really wanting to take it to the next level, and you’re ready to tear some walls down so you can find your voice, and build a personal brand that feels purposeful and aligned with who you really are, DM me the word ME!!

Here is what I’ve learned about putting yourself out there…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1️⃣ You HAVE to take the first step even though it’s all you have!! Everything we do is a stepping stone that upgrades us to the next level, and the MORE we try and figure it all out start to finish the more fear will tell us NO!  2️⃣ You absolutely NEED support, it’s non negotiable but stop telling people your dreams who don’t understand and then cry when they tell you it’s a bad idea. The truth is that a lot of us feel alone because we don’t have the RIGHT support. Not everyone is meant to understand and support ALL parts of us. It doesn’t mean we ditch our relationships, it just means there is a specific place for someone else to come into your life.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3️⃣ Nobody else will do it like you! Sure there are probably thousands of other people with a similar story, or trying to pursue the same thing, but what you carry is SO divinely unique. The more this revelation sinks deep, the more we realize comparison may be the dumbest thing we could ever live by.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4️⃣ You need to have faith!! This isn’t religion, it’s fact. We all have faith in SOMETHING. Faith is having complete trust or confidence in someone or something. Maybe your faith is trusting and believing that things just don’t ever work out for you. That is you putting your faith into something!! My faith is in the fact that God created me and put me on this planet ON PURPOSE for a purpose, and whether you believe in God or not, THAT faith has a higher frequency than the faith you put in the belief that things just don’t work out for you.  I’m looking for THREE women who are ready to take the first step, You KNOW deep down you have something to share. You’ve been wishing you had the courage to show up online authentically and START but FEAR has been your friend and you’re ready to overcome.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If this is you, DM me the word ME ⬅️

What if we valued rest as much as we valued productivity? What if through rest, we were able to become more productive, creative, and alive!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Imagine if once a week we had the opportunity to completely disconnect and recharge, connect with our loved ones, and take time for ourselves to reflect? No errands, events on the calendar, to do lists, extra curricular activities, work demands, social media consuming our time.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
What if we didn’t feel like we NEED an extra day in the week because we simply prioritized an extended period of rest for ourselves and our family.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Well, we totally can but the choice is ours. It’s not always an easy choice because there are always something fighting for our time.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Here are a few things I like to do to prepare for my 24 hours of rest from Friday evening to Saturday evening.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1️⃣ Make sure the house is clean so I can fully enjoy our space and be present.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2️⃣ Figure out what tasks NEED to get done before Friday evening, and release the rest to be returned to on Sunday or Monday.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3️⃣ Ask our kids what they’d like to do together as a family. Sometimes we play games, have a movie night, invite another family or friend to join us or bake something special. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4️⃣ Last but not least when we’re ready to turn off... We like to start our evening by lighting a candle (or multiple candles) to signal the start of our rest. I’m never without my favourite candles from @epiphanyandco_ ☝️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
To be honest, rest takes practice, especially when we are used to going nonstop and always DOING! So join me this Friday evening by welcoming in rest and saying yes to more agenda-less days as we say goodbye to 2022 and head into the new year!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I don’t know about you but I want to start 2023 from REST not from a place of hustle...

About two years ago, I was ready to throw in the towel on business. In fact, I looked at my husband Tim and said "I don't want to do this anymore." My anxiety was at an all time high because the business I had started, turned out to be the complete opposite of what I had hoped for. I endured all of the things that people fear when taking a risk and for the first time, I understood why most people don't do it. All of a sudden, It felt like
every area of my life was suffering, and everything I was so sure of, was crumbling around me.

Fast forward to today and not only am I still standing but I am thriving (most days, because I am still human). I'm no longer gasping for air because the weight of anxiety is too heavy. I am BACK in business doing what I've always loved, and I feel more aligned than ever. I have more self awareness and confidence, I have fewer more meaningful relationships, and I am currently planning my next BIG adventure with my family for 2023 (stay tuned for that!). To be honest, 2022 was probably the best year of my life. I have more freedom and joy, and I know this is just the beginning.

⬇️ HERE’S HOW I DID IT ⬇️

➡️ A lot of inner healing because I realized there are things hidden in our subconscious that cause us to react or make decisions we don’t fully understand. Even the seemingly small things are significant.

➡️ Detached my identity from my biz and the things I DO. I am not my success in business or my failures. 

➡️ Got back up and started again because THIS is what excellences. It's not about perfection and getting it right the first time. The road to true untethered success
requires excellence in all areas of our life.

💗 For those currently struggling, I want you to know, sometimes we have to take the time to rebuild our foundation. What might look like a step backward, could actually be the thing you need to launch yourself forward.

If you've ever felt like throwing in the towel, I
can promise you that what you're experiencing today, won't be the same as tomorrow if you just choose to keep putting one foot in front of the other.

Feeling like you lose motivation when engagement is low? Here are three things to consider! ⬇️

1️⃣ Are you DEEPLY rooted to your why? Staying connected and reminding yourself why you are even showing up on IG is really important. If your why doesn’t make you cry, it’s not big enough. Maybe you just need to remind yourself of your why, or maybe you need a new why! Also, ask yourself if this… Would I continue to show up even if no one else started following me? Something I told myself is that I will continue to show up on here even if I never gained another follower or new eyeball on my content. I’m here to serve who ever is watching and if that’s one person, I’m committed to them.

2️⃣ Every time you show up on stories or make a piece of content, you are planting a seed. Now remember, we don’t get to eat the fruit and veg the moment we plant the seed. There is a process and we need to remind ourselves of that. The growing season might seem slow be we have to trust the process 💗

3️⃣ We must remember that motivation is what gets us started, but discipline is what keeps us going. If you worked out at the gym and didn’t see the abs you were hoping to gain, show up in 3 months, would you stop? Well maybe if you weren’t disciplined 😆 but you would be aware of that right? We need to adopt the same sort of discipline into our social media strategy!!! Don’t give up just because your reels aren’t going viral after 2 months of consistency. Give it a year at least before you re evaluate or make a big shift in your content☝️too many of us give us before we get to see the break through, so keep posting and pressing on!!!

These are all things that we will develop when we work together 💗 From getting clarity on who you are and WHY you’re doing what you’re doing to taking massive action on a strategy that feels aligned with you and allows you yo show up on Instagram authentically AND confidently.

I’m turning myself in on this one, because I’ve spent YEARS in judgment…  You ASSUMING what other people are going to think of you = judgment.  You DECIDING what is right or wrong for someone else = judgment. 
 You forming thoughts about people and criticizing them in your mind = judgment.

You telling yourself you aren’t good enough = judgment.  There are SO many ways we walk in judgment toward ourselves and toward others and it’s often expected that we have an opinion on everything these days. Did you know the definition of an opinion is “a view or judgment formed about something, not necessarily based on fact or knowledge.” 🤯 What if we were never meant to carry the weight of all that knowledge?  The more I RELEASE judgment in my mind and heart, the more free I get which then produces more external freedom.  You might not think your judgments are hurting anyone, but the truth is that we REAP what we SOW. Your judgment is hurting YOU.   I don’t share this IN judgment… I share it from my own experience and it’s been too big of a breakthrough not to share. My own judgment wasn’t hurting the people I secretly judged, it was only hurting me.  I promise, the more we can get away from this way of living, the more free we will be from the INSDIE ➡️ OUT…  Have you ever thought of it this way before?

Stop letting the rules keep you from showing up!!

Imperfect action will ALWAYS get you further than waiting or not sharing at all☝️

When I work with my clients, my goal is to have them feeling confident about showing up and getting into a groove of consistency and THEN we can start implementing “rules” or strategies that are specific to THEIR audience.

We have to remember that Instagram isn’t a one size fits all, and we have to be willing to take imperfect action so that we CAN figure out what works and what doesn’t!!

Don’t even get me started on Salt Bae… I didn’t even know this guy a few months ago until me and @iammorgangillis fell into a midnight rabbit hole, absolutely mesmerized by this man and his weirdness…  After watching him for way longer than we should have, we both went to investigate where this dude’s restaurants were and how we could get our hands on one of these steaks.  The funny part is that, I’m not even a big steak fan, but here I am browsing the internet, fantasizing about an $800 steak with my friend when we probably should have been sleeping 😂🥩  But here is what that moment taught me ANd reminded me…  ➡️ It doesn’t matter how great your product is, if no one knows who you are.  ➡️This guy could probably still have a successful restaurant business without ever showing his face online, but he shows up in all of his awesome weirdness and people flipping LOVE IT (49 million peeps to be exact!) Do you ever find yourself hitting the refresh button after posting a reel…wishing, hoping and praying it does well or maybe even goes viral? I have 😆😅 and here is what I’ve discovered after 4 months of posting consistently.  1. I wasn’t even ready to go viral…What do I mean by that? Well… going viral just to go viral, literally means nothing. I had a reel hit 1.2 million views about 6 months ago, and while it may have boosted my engagement, it actually meant nothing for my business because my instagram account wasn’t optimized AND I wasn’t clear on who I was serving.   I gained some followers and some haters 😂, but quickly ended up losing them because that piece of content was strictly “entertainment” and it had nothing to do with my niche. It simply wasn’t aligned!  2. Your goal shouldn’t be just for anyone to see your content. Less eyeballs on your content doesn’t equate to less sales or less growth. The goal of your content should be to serve the people who are following you. 100 aligned eyeballs is better than 1.2million eye balls that don’t actually have any interest in your offer.  3. When I started treating content creation like my full time job, I started to see different results. Sure that could be numbers, but for me it’s been more connection with people and more aligned clients!   Remember, You get out what you put in, and when you pair clarity with consistency, it’s only a matter of time before you start to see results. You can’t expect to put an hour of time in once a week and expect to see massive results, and if you don’t know WHO you’re speaking to, it’s kind of like throwing spaghetti at the wall and hoping it sticks. Clarity and consistency are BFFs and you really can’t have one without the other!  If you don’t feel like you have clarity OR consistency down… I’d love to help!! Stop letting the big picture prevent you from taking action TODAY… 👊🏼  I had a conversation last week with a client of mine, and she shared with me that although she was REALLY excited about everything we’ve been talking about like sharing her story, helping women become resilient and living life on purpose… There was a moment where she realized there were some much bigger and more important issues that she felt she needed to fight for.  And I have to admit, I’ve had those thoughts before too and it reminded me of how I executed my previous design business. I had such a BIG PICTURE established in my mind of what I wanted to do, how I wanted my life to look like, and what I wanted to accomplish but I failed to zoom back in and focus on the micro steps that would allow me to build on a firm foundation. 😅  Here was my observation based on her story and mine…  ➡️ ONLY focusing on the big picture, is like trying to get to get to the top of the stairs in one step.⬅️  Focusing ONLY on the big picture can do TWO things…  1️⃣ It can cause us to freeze and not take any action at all because our vision and big picture thinking is SO big that we can’t even wrap our heads around how we’re going to go from A-Z. So we just don’t take action at all and stay at the bottom of the stairs.  OR  2️⃣ We can throw ourselves into it before we’re ready and overlook the micro steps that actually build character and skills needed in order to get to our desired destination. (This is what I did! 👀) I also don’t recommend this.   The truth is, it’s a bit of a balancing act. It’s knowing when to walk and when to run. When to take a risk, and when to wait just a little bit longer. It’s being honest with yourself, trusting the process and being in it for the long game. It’s being okay with growing slow, but also taking massive action on the one step that is in front of you TODAY. It’s trusting your intuition in the little things so you will be ready for the bigger things. It’s zooming out and zooming back in.  I’ve found myself on both ends of the spectrum and all I can say is:  It’s ONE STEP AT A TIME!!

Stop getting discouraged when numbers drop! I know it hurts the ego and sometimes it makes you want to show up less because there are fewer people watching but here are a few things to consider.

1️⃣ If 200 people loved following you and watching your stories for nutrition advice and now you’re talking about parenting and those 200 people are no longer watching. That’s okay! Maybe they don’t have kids 👀 if that’s the case, you don’t want those eyeballs on your page anyway because they are not your ideal customer.

2️⃣ Is your lack of numbers really affecting your sales? We have to remember that followers and insights on IG are not always reflective of the number in our bank account, and if you’re building a brand and monetizing this app, that is more important than how many people are seeing your stories.

3️⃣ Have you given it a year of consistency? This is huge! So many of us want to put a few weeks in and see instant results and it just doesn’t work like that. It doesn’t work in the gym and it doesn’t work on IG. I do recommend focusing on consistency after gaining clarity in who you are serving and how exactly you help them!

4️⃣ Remember that 100 views = 100 people!!!! 1000 views = 1000 people ☝️ no matter the number that feels “low” to you, you have to remember that these are real human beings watching you and engaging with you. I think the longer we are on IG the more numb we can become to numbers. Stop looking at people as numbers and start looking at them as people 💗 if you’ve got 1 person watching your stories every day, that means you have 1 potential client or customer and that’s a WIN!!

Trust the process my friend!!!

How do you have energy to show up online with kids?
How do you have energy to workout?
How do you have energy to do all the things?
 I’ve asked that question (to myself) about other people as well.  The truth is, I don’t always have energy.  I don’t always FEEL like posting content, working out, getting myself ready for the day, waking up early. If I’m being REALLY honest, in the moment, I OFTEN don’t feel like it.  What I’ve learned over the last 11 years from becoming my own boss, growing businesses, failing businesses and raising three small kids is this:  ➡️How you do one this, is how you do everything. Maybe you feel like every area of your life is a hot mess express, and you might not have capacity to do it all at the same time. THAT’S OKAY! Pick ONE THING! I guarantee if you can overcome ONE thing in your life, it will trickle over into other areas. It doesn’t matter how you start, it matters that you start!  ➡️You need to CREATE energy! Energy isn’t just given to some people and not others. Your motivation is temporary and your desire for pleasure is FAR greater than the desire to be uncomfortable. We KNOW what we need to do, we just don’t do it, and the quicker we can take action on the things we don’t FEEL like doing, the sooner we will overcome the mountain in front of us. When I make time for the things I don’t have energy for, I end up getting more energy. Netflix won’t give you energy, scrolling nonstop on IG won’t give you energy, thinking about your dreams and never taking action will NOT give you energy. It will TAKE energy!  It’s time to turn up the temperature of your life. You are capable of more! Stop sitting on the sidelines praying that the coach will call you up off the bench. Stand up, walk over and say “Hey Coach, I’d like to play!”  If you’re tired of playing small, drained from fear and comparison constantly holding you back BUT you deeply desire more MONEY, FULFILLMENT AND FREEDOM to be your most authentic self… It’s time to get up…  It’s time to get aligned ✨💗  If you’re ready stop watching from the sidelines, I’d LOVE to be your coach!  DM me the word ENERGY to learn more 💃

“I can’t do that!”
“I’ll never _______.”
“That’s great for you but I can’t _____.”

How many times in the run of a day do you catch yourself thinking or saying crap like this?

Fear is disguising itself behind circumstances, limiting beliefs and excuses.

Forget views and follows and focus on👇

1. Your ACTUAL goals!
When we talk about growth on IG, we’re often referring to views and followers but if those views and new eyeballs are not converting to paying customers or clients, then what are you really building? When you keep your eyes on your goals, it becomes easier to create content with those goals in mind. Views do not automatically equal sales, so focus on creating content that nurtures and brings value to your people. 

2. Connection with your current followers.  Instagram tracks when someone engages with any given person, this includes comments, likes, profile views, and DMs. By making an effort to genuinely connect and communicate with people, you not only boost the algorithm but more importantly you start to build relationships with people and that is what this is all about. Spend at least 30 minutes a day connecting with the people who are already engaging with your content. The best way to do this is through DMs but also make sure you’re engaging with other peoples content as well.

3. Understand and analyze your target market! Your target market is basically the people who are most likely to buy your products or services! These are the people whose desires, values and needs most closely align with what your business can offer them. Ultimately, they’re already looking for what you have. The more clearly you define your target market, the better you can understand how and where to reach your ideal potential clients/customers. The more you know, the better you can serve aka create content that doesn’t feel like throwing spaghetti at the wall. A great way to gather information from your target audience, once you’ve figured out who you want to serve, is through questionnaires and surveys!

4. Remember why you’re doing this work!
It can be really easy to let IG growth drain you, but the truth is, you likely didn’t start with the intention to get a bunch of followers. Sometimes we just have to let go and find joy in the journey. Focus on your mission and the rest will follow! Remember… PATIENCE my friend. Building a biz online is a marathon not a sprint!

This is only my second summer since I was a teenager that I haven’t chosen to work my evenings and weekends as a wedding photographer or doing B2C client work, and after a rough couple of years finding my way, I finally feel like I’m on the right path.

When you live somewhere that has mostly cold weather and winter for 7-8 months of the year, seasonal work becomes a way of life for many. It certainly was work I enjoyed but eventually I realized I wanted more freedom. I think for years I believed not working for someone else was the ultimate freedom, but what I realized is that for me it was just the first step…but don’t be fooled, you can be chained to a business just as much, if not more, as you could be chained to a boss or someone else’s schedule.

I’ve spent years trying to “build a business” and was always willing to do whatever it took to make a dream happen, but now my pursuit is building a life.

I think the reason so many of us are unhappy is because we are building our lives around our careers and businesses and not building our careers and businesses around our lives. 

So many people including myself, fail to ask themselves “what kind of lifestyle do I want to live?”… before jumping headfirst into a new endeavour 👀 Been there!

Now I lead with, will this fit our lives? Is it in alignment with how I want to spend my days?

If the answer is no, I’m not doing it 😂 and neither should you!

I can promise you, there is an endless amount of opportunities and ways to merge your ideal lifestyle with your gifts, passions and talents.

It just takes time, being honest with yourself and the courage to believe that you can 🤍

Having the freedom to enjoy my summers without missing out on any of the juicy stuff, is just the beginning of my freedom quest.

I hope that this encourages you to step into the freedom your heart is searching for ❤️

I’ve completed the 75 Hard challenge not once, but twice. Each time, it’s pushed me in incredible ways, even though I haven’t always come out on top. In fact, I’ve faced more failures than successes, but when I reflect, my real failure was giving up altogether. I still stand by the 75 Hard challenge because I believe many of us underestimate our potential. We often say it’s too hard or that we can’t do it, but deep down, do we truly want to do it? 😅😬

It’s perfectly fine if we don’t, but it’s astonishing how much we can handle beyond our doubts. If you’re struggling with discipline, self-confidence, or self-trust, committing to anything for 75 days will push your boundaries.

So, why 75 Slow? It’s like the familiar 75 challenge I know and love, but with a more deliberate, feminine touch and a slower pace. This challenge isn’t just about ticking tasks off a list; it’s about approaching each one with intention and listening to your body. It involves practices like cycle syncing, daily journaling, and reflection, and a commitment to reaching the finish line, even if there are slip-ups or tough days.

If you’re struggling to take action on something you know you need to do, here’s the truth: there may never be a “perfect” time. Life will always throw demands at us, and there will always be things we fear missing out on. But what if you worked with what you have? What if you didn’t have to miss out on anything? 75 Slow is all about slowing down and saying “yes” to yourself, even when there’s a never-ending list of other things you “should” be tending to.

So, here I stand, ready to take on 75, and it wouldn’t be the same without sharing this journey 😅😆

I totally get the urge to buy a whole new outfit for every trip, event or outing… I also get the “my wardrobe sucks” feeling and admit that I sometimes feel like my style would be better if I had more to spend.

So I’m challenging myself to be more creative because really, good fashion isn’t about how big your budget is. It’s what you can do with what you have.

Here’s a few tips on how you can get creative with your wardrobe:

1️⃣ Instead of buying the entire outfit, buy one new item that you can pair with other pieces you already own or pick your jumping off point or thing you’re most excited about and build from there, maybe it’s the shoes, an accessory or the top. 

2️⃣ Re-arrange your closet! Sometimes you need to see things with fresh eyes. I like to move things around in my closet every once in a while, especially the stuff that is sitting at the back that you don’t see all the time.

3️⃣ Think outside the box! Shop your partners closet, try wearing a swimsuit as a bodysuit, or an unexpected article of clothing that you wouldn’t normally wear. Think nightgowns, PJs, the sky’s the limit.

4️⃣ Mix and Match! Be intentional about not reaching for the same things that you think go together. Lay a pair of pants out and visualize all your different tops with those pants and don’t be afraid to try something unexpected.

5️⃣ Try throwing oversized sweaters over dresses you own and wear the dress as a skirt!! You can also wear a belt under the sweater if you need to do a sweater tuck.

6️⃣ Ask a friend!! Sometimes having literal fresh eyes on your clothes is the best thing ever. Someone else’s wardrobe always looks shinier than our own. Ask a friend to put something together for you, I bet it won’t be what you’d do. Ps. Make sure you ask the right friend 😜
